        "option_b_result": "CORRECT - For a crucial warning about a potential defect that needs to reach a broad external audience (customers, regulatory bodies) with precision and official documentation, a comprehensive press release issued through official company channels is the BEST method. It provides a formal, controlled, and widely distributable statement that can be accurately tracked and referenced, ensuring consistent and official information dissemination, which is vital for managing external communications.",
        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - Direct phone calls are good for personal communication but are not scalable for a broad external audience and do not provide an official, documented record for regulatory bodies or all customers.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - An internal memo is for internal communication only and would not reach external customers or regulatory bodies. It's entirely inappropriate for external, crucial warnings.",
